</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-24_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-25_ pf-text-1">According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), in 2019/20, there were approximately 693,000 non-fatal injuries at work in Great Britain. Of these, around 111,000 injuries required more than seven days of absence from work.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-27_ pf-text-1">Proper recording of accidents, including first aid incidents, is essential for accurately assessing risks, identifying trends, and implementing preventive measures.







