<br>
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-57_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-58_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training </strong>- Ensure that designated first aiders receive adequate training in first aid procedures, including accident recording.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-60_ pf-text-1"><strong>Documentation</strong> - Maintain a comprehensive accident book or electronic record to document all workplace incidents, including first aid interventions.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-62_ pf-text-1"><strong>Review and analysis</strong> - Regularly review accident records to identify trends, hazards, and areas for improvement.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-64_ pf-text-1"><strong>Communication</strong> - Encourage open communication among employees regarding safety concerns and incidents, fostering a proactive safety culture.









</li></ul><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-66_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Proper training of first aiders and personnel responsible for accident recording is essential to ensure timely and accurate documentation of incidents. Additionally, maintaining clear communication channels and fostering a culture of safety can further enhance accident recording practices.<br>
